Package com.github.crashdemons.playerheads.api

Interface HeadType

public interface HeadType
Object representing the type of Head supported by PlayerHeads. You can obtain the headtype for various things through API methods - to compare head types, you can use equals() This categorizes the head generally by entity type and does not retain user details (username/uuid/texture).
Author:
crashdemons (crashenator at gmail.com)

    • isPlayerHead

      boolean isPlayerHead()
      Checks whether the skulltype uses a playerhead material internally. This indicates that either the skulltype is PLAYER or a mob without a vanilla head item, generally. Note: This does not necessarily indicate the material of the head - On certain server versions, even Player-Head items are variants of Skeleton skulls.
      Returns:
      true: the skulls is implemented using a playerhead. false: the skull has a different associated item

    • isVanilla

      boolean isVanilla()
      Determines if a head of this type is implemented with a vanilla mob head or not [for the current server version].
      Returns:
      whether the head of is implemented with a vanilla mob head

    • getImplementationDetails

      com.github.crashdemons.playerheads.compatibility.SkullDetails getImplementationDetails()
      Get the underlying bukkit implementation details for the head on this server version. Includes things like the material id for blocks, items, skinnability, etc.

      Since 5.2.11, you can access the resulting object through the PlayerHeads Compatibility API

      Returns:
      an object providing implementation details
